## 13. Overall Assessment

**Grade: B+ (7.5/10)**

**Strengths:**
- Clean, well-architected core pipeline with battle-tested design decisions (bf16, no cuDNN SDPA, FP32 encoder)
- Thorough testing (27 tests, streaming parity, ONNX export)
- Clean data (595h, 0 missing files, 0 speaker leakage)
- Proven convergence at small scale (T16 100h test)
- Good documentation (plan, milestones, review reports)
- Active issue tracking and fixing (dead code removal, config fixes, RNG state preservation)

**Weaknesses:**
- ~30% of planned features not implemented (mostly augmentation + advanced validation)
- Streaming ONNX is not production-ready (KV cache needs nn.Module wrapper)
- v2.1 streaming is not implemented
- Validation uses only CTC (AED decode missing — WER numbers are misleading)
- Config coverage is thin (no Small model configs, no v2.1 full config)
- Several small dead code items remain
- Tokenized manifest may have stale/partial coverage

**Verdict:** The project is **ready for M9** (full v2 Tiny training on 595h). The core pipeline is solid, the data is clean, and the configuration is correct. The remaining milestones (M10-M16) need additional feature work and cloud budget, but the foundational infrastructure is in place. Fixing the critical items (AED validation decode, tokenized manifest coverage) before M9 would improve signal quality during the long training run.
